::The Eight S's Framework::Which of Birchard's "Eight S's" refers to using second-person pronouns ("you") to activate brain regions that interpret social signals?{
~Simplicity #Simplicity is about short sentences and familiar vocabulary, not social pronouns
~Specificity #Specificity is about concrete vs. abstract language (pelican vs. bird), not pronouns
~Stirring language #Stirring language is about emotional words that bypass cognitive processing
=Social content #"Social content" is Birchard's 7th S, referring to human-centered writing that activates brain regions interpreting social signals. Research shows readers infer character traits within 650 milliseconds when reading human-centered language, and second-person pronouns ("you") significantly improve learning retention compared to third-person text. Using "you" and "I" makes email feel like social interaction, not just information transfer.
}

